commit.message:
Return 1 to indicate error from main()

The statement 'return false;' was most likely to end up indicating successful exit 
by returning a 0 value, when failure seems to be intended.

This was flagged as a warning in the Debian Clang Archive Rebuild.

commit.message: Update SConstruct

Merge pull request #11 from xtaran/master

Merge changes from Debian: LDFLAGS → LINKFLAGS + Google Code → GitHub in man pages
Fix home page links in man pages, too

SConstruct: s/LDFLAGS/LINKFLAGS/

It turns out that scons uses its own name for this. Because they can,
I guess.  Propagating LDFLAGS is needed for hardening flags on Debian,
and in any case the current code does not make too much sense, since
LDFLAGS is ignored.

Fall back to checking XDG locations for config files.

If --config wasn't passed and $HOME/.xsettingsd doesn't
exist, fall back to the locations suggested by the XDG Base
Directory Specification (http://goo.gl/8AX6Lb). Add tests
for the new code.

(This was requested by Krytarik Raido and Unit 193.)

Make tests work with source-only libgoogletest.

Debian distributes libgoogletest a.k.a. libgtest in source
form now, so update SConstruct to build it from
/usr/src/gtest/src.

Also, I am regretting using SCons so hard right now. :-(
update README for google code turndown

Merge pull request #7 from derat/fgetc

Don't cast fgetc()'s return value to a char.

Don't cast fgetc()'s return value to a char.

Fix an issue described by Mihai Moldovan: int values
returned by ConfigParser::FileCharStream::GetCharImpl() were
cast to chars, resulting in EOF getting lost.

Merge pull request #5 from David-Bristol/negative-value-bugfix

Bugfix: allow negative int values.

Bugfix: allow negative int values.
ConfigParser::ReadInteger can handle these, but ::ReadValue was never
calling ::ReadInteger if the leading character was a - (minus) sign.
This makes the input to xsettingsd consistent with the output of
dump_xsettings.
